Shell
{
"application": "Shell",
"details": "This script is written in bash and designed for Arch Linux installation. It features a menu-driven interface for installing various software, including desktop environments, development tools, office apps, and more. It also provides options for configuring network settings, fonts, and system tools. The script utilizes the pacman package manager and the AUR (Arch User Repository) for installing packages. The script is highly configurable with user input options throughout the installation process. It includes functions for checking system requirements, installing and removing packages, configuring system settings, and managing user accounts.",
"requirements": [
"bash",
"pacman",
"AUR (Arch User Repository)",
"Network connection",
"Root privileges"
]
}
